      <T n="text">0xBDB0C86E<!--Sims can start their journey towards becoming a Fairy by researching at the Mossveil Fairy Hub, on the Computer, on a Bookshelf, or by asking a Fairy how to transform. <font color="#199C2C"><b>Fairy Seedlings</b></font> can be obtained by ordering one on the Computer or asking for one from a Fairy. Sometimes Fairies are kind enough to gift a Seedling when asked how to transform.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_FairyJourneyBecomeFairy_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:908fadc79fc75390</T>
      <T n="text">0xB5084927<!--Fairy Seedlings are not normal seeds and can be planted in Garden Pots, Planter Boxes, or the Terrain. Planting one summons <font color="#199C2C"><b>Mother Nature</b></font> who will charm the Sim with a potion and instruct them to complete their transformation at <font color="#199C2C"><b>Moondrop Springs</b></font> in <font color="#199C2C"><b>Everdew</b></font>. Once a Sim has traveled there, they can complete their Fairy transformation in the Spring's waters.--></T>
    </U>
